One of the most bizarre ideas Kozyrev had with his analysis of time as matter was that right-handed molecules like glucose and fructose absorb the flow of time and slow it down and thus some have a "shielding property" iirc. What happens when astronomers try to do nutrition.

Lactate is generally left-handed. A surprising right-hand molecule is apparently menthol that I posted about having similar effects to Progesterone on Galactose (another right-handed molecule) metabolism. I don't know enough about chemistry to make sense of this to be honest.
